.chimerathemes.com/">ChimeraThemes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.wpbundle.com/">WPBundle</a> vs. <a href="http://catalysttheme.com/">Catalyst Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://headwaythemes.com/">Headway Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://alohathemes.com/">Aloha Themes</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://www.kreativethemes.com/">KreativeThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.dessign.net/">Dessign</a></p><p><a href="http://press75.com/">Press75</a> vs. <a href="http://themes.bavotasan.com/">Themes by Bavotasan</a></td></tr><tr class="row-5 odd"><td class="column-1">April 14</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.dev4press.com/">Dev4Press</a> vs. <a href="http://www.indonez.com/">Indonez</a></p><p><a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themewarrior.com/">ThemeWarrior</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.wpzoom.com/">WPZoom</a> vs. <a href="http://www.vivathemes.com/">Viva Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.pagelines.com/">Pagelines</a> vs.<a href="http://wonderthemes.com/"> Wonder Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://gorillathemes.com/">Gorilla Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://wpshower.com/">WPShower</a></p><p><a href="http://diythemes.com/">DIYThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-force.com/">ThemeForce</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://tokokoo.com/">Tokokoo</a> vs. <a href="http://standardtheme.com/">Standard Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://thethemefoundry.com/">Theme Foundry</a> vs. <a href="http://themefuse.com/">ThemeFuse</a></td></tr><tr class="row-6 even"><td class="column-1">April 18</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16931">Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 3</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 06:44:43 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:38;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"WPCandy: The WPCandy Show, episode 1: “One is the loneliest number”";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16893";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/4yJa0f2YGtk/ep-001";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6439:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16893"><img src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wpcandyshowep1-teaser.jpg" alt="" title="WPCandy Show episode 1 (teaser)" width="600" height="282" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16917" /></a></p><p>I&#8217;m excited to present the first episode of a new production here at WPCandy: The WPCandy Show. We love creating blog posts about WordPress, <a href="http://wpcandy.com/podcasts">podcasts about WordPress</a>, and now, finally, we can create videos about WordPress.</p><p>The WPCandy Show, our first video podcast, will bring you the week&#8217;s biggest WordPress news in a quick video format. We&#8217;ll soon have the show available in other subscription formats such as iTunes and YouTube as well.</p><p>The video is embedded just after the jump, as well as the show notes. If you have a minute, take a look and let us know what you think!</p><p><span id="more-16893"></span></p><div id="the-show-player"> </div><h3>Show Notes</h3><p>This week on the show a number of news topics were mentioned:</p><ul><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/wordpress-all-in-one-for-dummies-now-available-on-amazon">WordPress All in One for Dummies is available on Amazon.</a></li><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness is underway.</a></li><li><a href="http://wordcampseattle.org/">WordCamp Seattle</a> is this upcoming weekend, and WPCandy will be there.</li><li>Joshua Strebel <a href="http://wpcandy.com/thinks/is-tumblr-the-new-wordpress">contributed an editorial</a> last week that was commented on quite a bit. It also put us on Hacker News for a while, bringing us a new traffic record!</li></ul><p>A number of WordPress videos were also mentioned during the show:</p><ul><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/allure-themes-pre-launch-preview">The pre-launch webinar for Allure Themes</a>.</li><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/adii-pienaar-interviewed-discusses-the-success-of-woothemes">A video interview with Adii Pienaar</a>.</li><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/mixergy-interview-with-collis-taeed-of-envato">Collis Ta&#8217;eed of Envato was interviewed on Mixergy</a>.</li><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/jason-schuller-interviewed-about-web-design">Jason Schuller was interviewed on Freelance Jam</a>.</li><li><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/the-making-of-an-obox-theme">We also have the time-lapsed creation of an Obox theme</a>.</li></ul><h3 id="copy-hide-trigger">Show Episode Transcript</h3><div id="copy-hide"> Welcome to The WPCandy Show, your weekly source of WordPress community news. This is episode #1, and I&#8217;m your host Ryan Imel.</p><p>On today&#8217;s show we have a new WordCamp coming up, an update on Theme Madness, and a new record for WPCandy. Let&#8217;s get to it.</p><p>Big news this week, WordPress All in One for Dummies is now available. This is another WordPress book authored by Lisa Sabin-Wilson, the author of WordPress for Dummies, though this time she is joined by Cory Miller of iThemes, Kevin Palmer of Convertiv, Andrea Rennick of WPeBooks, and Michael Torbert of All in One SEO Pack. The book is currently available through Amazon, but will hit brick and mortar retailers on the 19th.</p><p>WPCandy&#8217;s own Theme Madness tournament is underway this month. For those who don&#8217;t know, Theme Madness is our game to determine the best WordPress theme vendor out there. Or at least, to determine which one can rally the most support. We are working through a bracket with 64 teams, and are currently wrapping up Round 1. Be sure to visit the WPCandy blog to see who wins the hand made WPCandy trophy.</p><p>WordCamp Seattle is happening this weekend, on Saturday. There are three tracks, a User Track, a Theming Track, and a Development Track. The special guest will be Alex King of Crowd Favorite, who will be interviewed at the end of the day by Nick Ohrn about his WordPress business success. Well, the other special guests will be the WPCandy crew, who will be there and liveblogging the whole thing, so you won&#8217;t miss any of the good stuff.</p><p>Big thanks to The Theme Foundry who powered us to attend WordCamp Seattle this year. Of course, The Theme Foundry isn&#8217;t the only one who can power WPCandy. Believe it or not, anyone can. See, at WPCandy we don&#8217;t take advertisers. Instead, we use a system where the community itself powers us. You can power a post, a day of content, a trip to a WordCamp, or simple a $5 monthly subscription. Every little bit helps us do what we do, and keep our content ad free. Head over to wpcandy.com/is/powered if you&#8217;re interested in helping us out.</p><p>We&#8217;ll be right back after this ad &#8212; no, I&#8217;m kidding. We don&#8217;t have those, remember?</p><p>Page.ly cofounder Joshua Strebel contributed an editorial to WPCandy last week, talking about how he has heard Tumblr described as having some of the strengths that WordPress has, and what that could mean. Be sure to read his editorial, and the 70 or so odd comments that follow. His editorial landed on Hacker News for a bit over the weekend, bringing in almost 8,000 uniques for us, a new daily traffic record. Thanks everyone, it&#8217;s exciting to see the site growing this way.</p><p>There were a number of interesting videos added to the site this week.</p><ul><li>The pre-launch webinar for Allure Themes was posted &#8212; Allure Themes will be WordPress themes for the ladies. And for me.</li><li>A video interview with Adii Pienaar of WooThemes</li><li>Collis Ta&#8217;eed of Envato was interviewed on Mixergy, and we have that posted</li><li>Jason Shuller of Press75 and Theme Garden was interview about web design on Freelance Jam.</li><li>And we have the time-lapsed video, the making of an Obox theme, as well.</li></ul><p>All of those videos can be found at wpcandy.com/watches.</p><p>That&#8217;s it for this week. Don&#8217;t forget to follow WPCandy on Twitter, friend us on Facebook, and if you&#8217;re feeling bold, power WPCandy so we can keep doing what we love. Have a good one, we&#8217;ll see you next week.</p></div><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16893">The WPCandy Show, episode 1: "One is the loneliest number"</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 04:41:40 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:39;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"WPCandy: Matt Mullenweg interviewed by Bloomberg at SxSW";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16913";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/UotpJ_b9vw8/matt-mullenweg-interviewed-by-bloomberg-at-sxsw";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:687:"<p></p><p>Matt Mullenweg, the founder of Automattic, was interviewed on Bloomberg while at SxSW a couple of weeks ago. In the interview, they talk about Matt&#8217;s background, the early days of WordPress, how Automattic came to be what it is today, and a bit about the competition.</p><p>One highlight for me was, &#8220;We&#8217;re at 12% of the web. I want that to be 20, 30, 40%.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16913">Matt Mullenweg interviewed by Bloomberg at SxSW</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 04:38:01 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Brian Krogsgard";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:40;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"WPTavern: WordPress And Its Cloudy Future";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=5246";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/Z7CZdg2--1E/wordpress-and-its-cloudy-future";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:543:"<p><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/forum/general-wordpress/2219-where-does-wordpress-go-here.html">Join in the conversation</a> and tell us where you think WordPress as a platform should go. </p>\n\n\n<p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/the-future-of-bbpress-lies-within-wordpress" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: The Future Of bbPress Lies Within WordPress">The Future Of bbPress Lies Within WordPress</a></li>\n</ol></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~4/Z7CZdg2--1E" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 01:30:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Jeffro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:41;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"WPCandy: WordPress loving PHP developers are in high demand";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16885";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/sUBxTYaCnJ0/wordpress-php-developer-jobs";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2124:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16885"><img src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/PHPjobs.png" alt="WordPress jobs for php developers" width="600" height="250" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-16889" /></a><br /> Do you love WordPress? Are you awesome with PHP? If so, there are job openings for you. Page.ly, Themify, Obox and Automattic are all looking for experienced PHP developers.</p><p>Themify is a commercial WordPress theme shop. They are looking for both a freelance (remote okay) PHP developer and a frontend (Toronto based) developer. Find all the information you need on <a href="http://themify.me/blog/hiring-fulltime-designer-freelance-developer">their blog post</a>.</p><p>Page.ly is a managed WordPress hosting provider. They are looking for a primarily PHP, but also jack-of-all-trades, developer. The position is full time, and you can work remote. Learn more on their <a href="http://page.ly/about/careers/">careers page</a>.</p><p>Obox is a commercial WordPress theme shop. They are looking for a full time PHP developer. You can work remotely, but they ask that you have at least some work-time overlap with GMT+2 timezone (Cape Town), which is 6 hours ahead of U.S. Eastern Time. Learn more on their <a href="http://www.obox-design.com/view_item.cfm/title/were-is-hiring">blog post</a>.</p><p>Automattic, the parent company to WordPress.com, always seems to be hiring. Currently they&#8217;re seeking folks fit for positions from Code Wrangler to Happiness Officer. Many of the positions ask for at least some proficiency in PHP. Check out all of their openings on the <a href="http://automattic.com/jobs/">jobs page</a>.</p><p>It seems PHP, and WordPress knowledge in general, is a skill in high demand. Do you know of other well known WordPress companies hiring? Share with us in the comments.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16885">WordPress loving PHP developers are in high demand</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 12 Apr 2011 21:53:44 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Brian Krogsgard";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:42;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"Weblog Tools Collection: Bloomberg Venture’s Matt Mullenweg Interview";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9879";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/zAti6Hz_GAk/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:695:"<p>If you&#8217;re curious about the history of <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, the infrastructure of <a href="http://automattic.com/">Automattic</a> and <a href="http://wordpress.com/">WordPress.com</a>, and the future of WordPress, don&#8217;t miss <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/video/68075030/">this fascinating interview</a> with WordPress founder <a href="http://ma.tt/">Matt Mullenweg</a>.</p>\n<p>You can see all four parts of the interview <a href="http://wordpress.tv/2011/03/28/bloomberg-mullenweg/">combined at WordPress.tv</a> or embedded below.</p>\n<p></p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/zAti6Hz_GAk" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 12 Apr 2011 13:00:38 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:43;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"Matt: Meaning of VaultPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=37961";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"http://ma.tt/2011/04/meaning-of-vaultpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:147:"<p>Douglas Van Bossuyt says <a href="http://www.douglasvanbossuyt.com/2011/02/06/what-vaultpress-means-to-me/">What VaultPress means to me</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 12 Apr 2011 05:46:34 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:44;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16870";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/2OWAbcFM1ng/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-2-voting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15329:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16870"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16871" title="Theme Madness Round 1 Day 2 voting" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnessround1day2-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>This week we will be running through Round 1 of <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness</a>, with eight games happening each day. Today’s games will be:</p><ul><li><a title="Graph Paper Press" href="http://graphpaperpress.com/">Graph Paper Press</a> vs. <a title="Panda Themes" href="http://pandathemes.com/">Panda Themes</a></li><li><a title="Theme Garden" href="http://www.themegarden.com/">Theme Garden</a> vs. <a title="BlogOhBlog" href="http://www.blogohblog.com/">BlogOhBlog</a></li><li><a title="ThemeJam" href="http://themejam.com/">ThemeJam</a> vs. <a title="Startbox" href="http://wpstartbox.com/">Startbox</a></li><li><a title="Organic Themes" href="http://www.organicthemes.com/">Organic Themes</a> vs. <a title="Storefront Themes" href="http://storefrontthemes.com/">Storefront Themes</a></li><li><a title="Theme Hybrid" href="http://themehybrid.com/">Theme Hybrid</a> vs. <a title="Xtreme Theme" href="http://xtreme-theme.com/">Xtreme Theme</a></li><li><a title="Pro Theme Design" href="http://prothemedesign.com/">Pro Theme Design</a> vs. <a title="Themes Kingdom" href="http://www.themeskingdom.com/en/page/home/23">Themes Kingdom</a></li><li><a title="Solostream" href="http://www.solostream.com/">Solostream</a> vs. <a title="ThemeShift" href="http://themeshift.com/">ThemeShift</a></li><li><a title="Crowd Favorite" href="http://crowdfavorite.com/">Crowd Favorite</a> vs. <a title="Working Wireframes" href="http://workingwireframes.com/">Working Wireframes</a></li></ul><p>All of the polls and instructions can be found just after the jump, so be sure to click through to have your voice heard. Voting will take place for the next 48 hours, and close at midnight on the 13th (Eastern Standard Time).</p><p>If you need a reminder, the rules can be found <a title="How to win your Theme Madness 2011 Trophy" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-rules">here</a>. Good luck to everyone playing!</p><p><span id="more-16870"></span></p><h3>Graph Paper Press vs. Panda Themes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4893015"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4893015"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4893015/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online survey</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Graph Paper Press on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/graphpaperpress">@GraphPaperPress</a> or <a title="Panda Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/pandathemes">@PandaThemes</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Graph Paper Press or Panda Themes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Theme Garden vs. BlogOhBlog</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4893055"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4893055"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4893055/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online survey</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Theme Garden on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/themegarden">@ThemeGarden</a> or <a title="BlogOhBlog on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/blogohblog">@BlogOhBlog</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Theme Garden or BlogOhBlog start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>ThemeJam vs. Startbox</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4893043"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4893043"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4893043/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="ThemeJam on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/themejam">@ThemeJam</a> or <a title="Startbox on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/wpstartbox">@WPStartbox</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either ThemeJam or Startbox start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Organic Themes vs. Storefront Themes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4893047"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4893047"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4893047/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">customer surveys</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Organic Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/organicthemes">@OrganicThemes</a> or <a title="Storefront Theme on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/storefronttheme">@StorefrontTheme</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Organic Themes or Storefront Themes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as 